  <notes>
    Completed 2026-07-01 as part of task 095 (atomic collapse).

    Reason for collapse:
      Task 095 chose the **optional parameters** design (over separate
      overload). C# forbids interface method signatures whose implementations
      diverge in parameter count — both `InvokePlaybookAi.cs` and
      `NullInvokePlaybookAi.cs` MUST have the exact widened signature the
      moment `IInvokePlaybookAi.cs` gains the new optional args, or the
      project fails to compile. Therefore the tasks 095 + 096 work is
      inherently atomic: interface + both impls + tests ship together.

    Task 096's explicit acceptance requirements were satisfied by task 095:
      - ✅ `InvokePlaybookAi.cs`: signature updated; `PlaybookRunRequest`
        built with `UserContext = userContext, Document = document`,
        `Parameters = parameters`, `DocumentIds = Array.Empty&lt;Guid&gt;()`.
      - ✅ Logging updated with `hasUserContext` + `userContextLength` +
        `hasDocument` + `documentTextLength` (presence + counts only per
        ADR-015 — no text bodies logged).
      - ✅ `NullInvokePlaybookAi.cs`: signature updated; kill-switch
        fail-fast semantics preserved (ADR-032 P3 pattern intact for
        both Phase 1 + Phase 2 consumers).
      - ✅ 3 new tests in `InvokePlaybookAiTests.cs`:
        `InvokePlaybookAsync_WithUserContextAndDocument_ForwardsToRequest`,
        `InvokePlaybookAsync_WithoutUserContextOrDocument_BackwardCompatibleRequestShape`,
        `NullInvokePlaybookAi_WithWidenedArgs_StillThrowsFeatureDisabled`.

    Verification:
      - Task 095 build + test verification IS task 096 build + test
        verification (same commit, same file set).
      - `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`: ✅ 0 errors / 19
        warnings (baseline preserved).
      - 94/94 relevant tests pass (InvokePlaybookAi + boundary + all
        consumer setups).

    See task 095 notes for the full change log + files-touched list.
  </notes>
</task>
